<a href="javascript:card_browser(274)">The Tale of Gil-galad</a><br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(8)">No Stranger to the Shadows</a> x 2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(852)">The Saga of Elendil</a><br>
O Elbereth! Gilthoniel!<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(190)">Power According to His Stature</a><br>
=Events=<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(924)">Secret Sentinels</a><br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(12)">A Ranger&#39;s Versatility</a><br>
<br>
SHADOW (35)<br>
=Minions=<br>
Bill Ferny, Swarthy Sneering Fellow<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(122)">Ulaire Attea, Keeper of Dol Guldur</a> x 2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(124)">Ulaire Cantea, Lieutenant of Dol Guldur</a> x 4<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(125)">Ulaire Enquea, Lieutenant of Morgul</a> x 2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(864)">Ulaire Nelya, Lieutenant of Morgul</a> x 4<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(129)">The Witch-king, Lord of Angmar</a> x 4<br>
=Possessions=<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(111)">Morgul Blade</a> x 2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(116)">The Pale Blade</a> x 2<br>
=Conditions=<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(103)">Black Breath</a> x 4<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(104)">Blade Tip</a> x 3<br>
=Events=<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(314)">Fear</a><br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(112)">Morgul Gates</a> x 4<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(89)">Relentless</a> Charge<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(985)">Stricken Dumb</a>    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> OVERVIEW<br>
The main focus behind the deck is making it as painful as possible for the opposing fellowship to even think about moving twice, while having a versatile fellowship of your own which should be able to double-move at least a couple of times. The fellowship is centred around Aragorn, Arwen, Legolas GL and elf allies. The shadow side is pure Nazgul, designed to get renowned fellowship destroyers, the Witch-king and Ulaire Cantea, out there as much as possible. Black Breaths and Blade Tips help support the &quot;slow the opposition down&quot; theme (just watch your opponent dive for the Sleep/Athelas). 70 cards might seem large for an Elf/Nazgul deck, but judicious use of Gwemegil&#39;s discard power and Elrond&#39;s card drawing should see you just about use the whole deck up (especially if your opponent is, as expected, unable to double move).<br>
I generally bid 3 burdens &#8212; it&#39;s no disaster if I don&#39;t go first as I&#39;ll often get a Nelya at site 2 (allowing me to bring out the Prancing Pony, that is if the other person isn&#39;t already playing it), and Nazgul can really do some damage going second (Weatherhills and Ford of Bruinen).<br>
<br>
FELLOWSHIP<br>
Aragorn KiE gets the spot ahead of RotN because every companion bar Legolas has the Aragorn signet &#8212; his healing ability is a critical part of this deck.<br>
Two copies of Ranger&#39;s Sword and Gwemegil help ensure that the important weapons get out early.<br>
Athelas and Secret Sentinels provide shadow condition removal.<br>
Sam pops up as burden removal then as a pincushion.<br>
Aragorn should get an Armor early on, important against Uruk-hai (Frodo with Sting and Mithril-coat is an underrated option against Uruks as well).<br>
Boromir can stick on the second Armor and basically wear any minion without being overwhelmed.<br>
Direct damage is a strength. Between them, Orophin and Rumil provide direct damage to every minion type except Nazgul (Arwen&#39;s specialty) while being healed by Galadriel. (Not to mention Aragorn&#39;s Bow and Legolas GL.)<br>
Thrarin exists as swarm protection/Balrog bait (as always).<br>
Pillars of the Kings is site 8 so that it can be played using Thror&#39;s Map (nothing worse than copping a Shores of Nen Hithoel and five Orcs when you are trying to double-move for the win).<br>
This deck probably performs least well against Nazgul, but hey, you&#39;ll be playing them too so it&#39;s all square.<br>
<br>
SHADOW<br>
Everybody says Nazgul are toast since the Flaming Brand arrived, but the Witch-king and Ulaire Cantea don&#39;t fear it &#8212; Cantea can discard those annoying weapons and the Witch-king is generally big enough to take the bonus and still win, particularly if he is with friends. And who&#39;s going to move on when one/both of those guys are left behind?<br>
A &quot;burden the Ring-bearer&quot; strategy is too hit-and-miss so I haven&#39;t worried about trying to create burdens or take advantage of them (eg no Nazgul swords, twilight Nelya or Dark Whispers). Instead, I&#39;ve just included an all-fierce combination.<br>
The four Nelyas are there to help set up the two most important early sites (Prancing Pony and Ford of Bruinen) if required.<br>
Ulaire Enquea is the large fellowship killer with his gametext and Attea is useful for combatting skirmish events.<br>
Pale Blades and Stricken Dumb will let you use the Witch-king to remove annoying conditions and weapons, while Fear will do the same for whichever ally is causing you the most frustration.<br>
Bill Ferny may be Greenleaf-bait, but when he doesn&#39;t get pinged away, he can sometimes be the factor which pushes a standard victory into an overwhelm.<br>
The only thing that will annoy your minions is Hobbit Stealths/Intuitions but the Morgul Gates should allow you to get out enough Nazgul to still do at least some damage early on.<br>
No Balrog because who wants to be only able to have one minion at site 5 (one who can&#39;t even travel to site 6)? I&#39;d much rather have the Witch-king and Cantea on the Bridge. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font class="bfont"> <a href="/lotr/decks/decks.php">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/lotr/decks/decks.php?reviews=23889"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=23889" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/lotr/main/join.php">Sign up for free!</A></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
